 data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Moon ☽</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-28163065 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="ea75af28-1630-4595-8504-663818c0edbf" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-3818c0ed"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-04663818">The moon, as pure feminine energy, can help with spiritual and emotional healing and is undoubtedly the most purifying method toclear crystals. Not only this, but the moon can be used to program any crystal for extra vitality. <br><br>1. Place crystals directly under moonlight, on a windowsill.<br>2. If your crystal can withstand water, consider placing it in a safe place outside for maximum clearing.<br>3. Full and new moons have the most powerful energy.<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-31e4a134 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-bf998df0 accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="edbf998d-f031-44a1-b4bb-6cb0fd481d05" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Sun ☼</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-8df031e4 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="edbf998d-f031-44a1-b4bb-6cb0fd481d05" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-b0fd481d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bb6cb0fd">The sun is another supercharging cleanser when it comes to clearing your crystals. Solar energies tend to be more ‘masculine’, and are better suited to programming, super-charging your crystal to give it drive and focus rather than healing. <br><br>1. Place your crystals in direct sunlight, or on a windowsill.<br>2. Leave them here for a short time only.<br>3. Clouds will not disrupt the clearing process.<br><br>Note: Not all crystals can withstand high or direct heat and will crack, whilst others will lose their colour if left for prolonged periods in the sun. Please consult the list below before placing any crystals in sunlight.<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-53d19478 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-053c183c accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="1d053c18-3c53-4194-b88e-50689db6e633" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Snow ❄</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-183c53d1 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="1d053c18-3c53-4194-b88e-50689db6e633" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-689db6e6"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-8e50689d">If you are fortunate enough to have access to freshly fallen snow, this is a quick and powerful way to clear your crystals.<br><br>1. Place in clean, dry snow.<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-0ec3f7d1 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-33d1fb87 accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="e633d1fb-870e-43f7-9164-6c4b6bba76e2" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Earth ✾</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-fb870ec3 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="e633d1fb-870e-43f7-9164-6c4b6bba76e2" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-4b6bba76"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-646c4b6b">This element remains very powerful as an effective way of cleansing your crystals: the Earth is their birthing place! <br><br>1. Bury your crystals in your yard or in an indoor house plant.<br>2.&nbsp;Depending on the depth of cleansing you feel is required, leave in soil for three, seven or eleven days.<br>3&nbsp;Alternate the areas and plants you use to clear your crystals, to preserve the individual energies of those plants.<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-58978599 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-e24e5e23 accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="76e24e5e-2358-4785-9982-b7e3e99eef9b" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Smoke</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-5e235897 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="76e24e5e-2358-4785-9982-b7e3e99eef9b" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-e3e99eef"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-82b7e3e9">I love to use smoke as a way of cleaning my crystals! I like to use Palo Santo, not only because it is a wood native to South America and reminds me of home, but because of its beautiful energetic clearing effects. It’s been used for centuries to clear negative energies; I love it!  You may use smudging already to clear your home of negative energies with sage, lavender, cedar, sweetgrass or incense: the same principle is used to clear your crystals. Using smoke as a clearing method is especially helpful for jewellery susceptible to corrosion underwater.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Hold the crystals over the burning smudge stick.<br></span><br>1. Allow the smoke to envelope your crystals for a short time, a minute perhaps. Longer depending on the depth <br>of clearing you feel is required.<br>2. Use a feather or fan to waft the smoke over your crystals, if need be.<br>3. Ensure a door or window is open to allow the smoke (and the energy it has cleared from your crystals) to leave the room.<br>4. Extinguish your smudge stick thoroughly.<br> </span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-a6143216 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-9bc20df9 accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="ef9bc20d-f9a6-4432-9660-f4c7892ec26b" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Sound ♪</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-0df9a614 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="ef9bc20d-f9a6-4432-9660-f4c7892ec26b" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-c7892ec2"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-60f4c789">Acoustic vibrations are very effective in clearing crystals through sound, removing negative or unwanted energy in the crystals. <br> There are numerous melodic methods to try: <br><br>1. Tuning forks: can be used by tapping the crystal gently against the fork. Move the fork around the crystals until it stops vibrating. Repeat this action until you feel the crystal is cleared. <br>2. Singing bowl: place the crystals around the bowl. Feel the vibrations once you move the mallet around the outer edges of the bowl. Continue until you feel the crystals have been cleared.<br>3. Bells: place the bell over your crystals and begin ringing. The vibration will cleanse your crystals very effectively!<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Super Power Crystals<br></span>Some crystals can actually cleanse other stones, with selenite, quartz, carnelian, amethyst and kyanite amongst these super-powered crystals.<br><br>1. Place a selenite slab under your crystals to clear and charge your crystals.<br>2. Place smaller crystals on an amethyst cluster to neutralise and clear them.<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-76cac1b4 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-6ba4738e accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="c26ba473-8e76-4ac1-b44d-597296552bc3" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Salt</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-738e76ca accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="c26ba473-8e76-4ac1-b44d-597296552bc3" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-7296552b"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-4d597296">This is another easy, effective and readily available method with which to clear your crystals. <br>Use whichever of the following methods feels best for you:<br><br>1. Natural salt water (i.e. sea water) is best, though using store-bought sea salt is also fine. <br>2. Place your crystals in a bowl of salt and bury them in it overnight. (You can use uncooked rice as an alternative.) <br>3. If you want to avoid the crystals physically touching the salt, place them in a bowl inside another bowl of salt. (A good idea for any pieces containing metal.)<br>4. Soak crystals in a bowl of salt water overnight or up to 48 hours. This will allow the energy to be drawn out of the crystals. <br>5. Dispose of the remains of the rice or salt back to the Earth: it has absorbed negative energy during the cleansing and should not be eaten or used.<br><br><span style="font-weight: bold;">Note: Not all crystals can be submerged in water and especially salt water without serious physical damage occurring. Please consult the list below before submerging any crystals.</span><br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-3455f156 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-c31eaab3 accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="2bc31eaa-b334-45f1-96ed-aabf3de21cc4" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Reiki</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-aab33455 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="2bc31eaa-b334-45f1-96ed-aabf3de21cc4" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-bf3de21c"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-edaabf3d">Reiki is a modern healing modality which uses life force energy to cleanse and heal. <br>You can use Reiki to clear your crystals, though for the greatest effectiveness, some training in Reiki is needed.<br><br>1. Place one hand over the crystal and feel its vibrations.<br>2. Ask the universal life force that the crystal be cleansed of any absorbed and negative energy no longer serving it. <br>3. Hold your hand over the crystal until you feel it has reverted to its original energetic state.<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-f3d93eb8 accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-c4c14898 accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="1cc4c148-98f3-493e-b8bc-9ad5bd0536b1" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Intention and Visualization</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-4898f3d9 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="1cc4c148-98f3-493e-b8bc-9ad5bd0536b1" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-d5bd0536"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bc9ad5bd">Clearing crystals through visualization allows you to clear them from anywhere, a great option if your usual tools are unavailable.<br><br>1. Hold your crystal in your hand and visualise white light washing over the stone. <br>2. Imagine a beam of white light emitting from your hand or your Third Eye.<br>3. Visualise all negativity and absorbed energy being washed out and away from your crystals.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pJipy mZVAk pf-09b58a0f accordion__item" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content.Wrapper"><button type="button" class="sc-pBlxj gYSgcm pf-b1c9772f accordion__header pf-anchor" data-header-id="36b1c977-2f09-458a-8ffb-9d0663f82d37" data-action="accordion2" data-preopen="false" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="icon_position accordion__arrow fa fa-chevron-right"></i> Pendulums</button><div class="sc-qYUWV exYsxy pf-772f09b5 accordion__content" mode="view" data-id="36b1c977-2f09-458a-8ffb-9d0663f82d37" data-pf-type="Accordion2.Content" style="display: none;"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-0663f82d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-fb9d0663">Pendulums are another tool used to help release energy from crystals. <br><br>1. Hold the pendulum over the crystals.<br>2. The pendulum will begin to rotate in the pattern normally equated with meaning ‘no’ as negative energy is cleared. <br>3. Once cleared, the pendulum will rotate in the opposite direction.<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-85c66648" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-0b4085c6 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--4"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-469ddf37" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-b946235f"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-da04aea1">How to Physically Clean Crystals<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--8 pf-c-md--8 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-df370b40" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-235f469d"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-5e0cb946">Handling, burying or leaving crystals in our bags and other regular uses can cause some residual build up on them. If your crystals are hard (like quartz):<br><br>1. Soak them in warm water with a little soap to loosen any dirt or grime. <br>2. Using a soft toothbrush, remove any persistent debris. <br>3. Soak the stones some more before rinsing. <br>4. Polish with a soft cloth. <br><br>To clean soft crystals, such as amber and selenite:<br><br>1. Use a soft cloth (like microfiber) to polish and clean crystals. <br>2. A clean makeup brush is also effective.<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-03abbf79" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-ee8f03ab pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-4262ee8f" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Divider" class="sc-qQKeD hpksip pf-67244262"><div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-9d33c840" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-95ba9d33 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--4"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-fbf1e16a" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-52dadddf"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-ebf6840c">When to Clear Crystals<br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--8 pf-c-md--8 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-e16a95ba" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-2d9d225a"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-cfef2d9d">When you receive your crystals from Shiny Storm, it is important to clear them so that you have welcomed them and they feel embraced into both your physical and energetic space. This crystal has travelled a long way to reach you: show it love and honour its arrival through some beautiful clearing and cleansing methods.<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-8ce500a9"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-bc2f8ce5">Once the crystals have been cleared upon arrival, there is no specific guide to when you should clear them again: rather, follow your intuition for what feels most effective. You will know, trust yourself!</span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-dddfd563"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-30f109eb">A crystal will absorb energy as it works with you to heal, set intentions and clear energy. Each has its own purpose and like us, needs a rest and a recharge from time to time. You may notice your crystal feeling particularly weighty, dull in colour or you may receive a message that it needs love and cherishing.<br>If you are attempting to address any kind of significant difficulties like a fight, illness or trauma, for instance, your crystals will serve you best if they are cleared before being used.<br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-cf0db3ce"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-a9d2cf0d">Over time, you will develop a loving relationship with your crystals. Listen to them, they will guide you best on how to harness their power.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-b7bf4212" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-5fafb7bf pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-e79a5faf" data-pf-type="Column"><div data-pf-type="Divider" class="sc-qQKeD hpksip pf-79af466e"><div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-49c222b8" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-9eaa49c2 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--4"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-054446af" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-712814aa"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-eda04073"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">⇾ Kryptonite and your Crystals</span><br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--8 pf-c-md--8 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-46af9eaa" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-14aa0955"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-66c6a766">Whilst crystals are amazing healing minerals, just like Superman and kryptonite, each can be damaged if exposed to certain environments or other base elements. <br></span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-0955f823"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-26c25faa">Some cannot be left in water: they’ll dissolve into sand! </span></p><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-f8230544"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-d8b77128">Others will crack if left in direct sunlight. Each crystal has its own needs and ‘feels’ better in certain environments, just like us! Caring for your stones and understanding which crystals can be exposed to which elements, will not only improve the efficacy of the healing energy within your stone, it will ensure they last longer within your home.<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-container="true" class="sc-pZopv bjKdkd pf-98f97ab3" data-pf-type="Section"><div class="sc-pQQXS iWCqut" style="max-width: 1170px;"><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-f26698f9 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--4 pf-c-md--4 pf-c-lg--4"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-7ceebe2a" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-5875da74"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-22cc433f"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">⇾ Damaged by water</span><br></span></p></div></div><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--8 pf-c-md--8 pf-c-lg--8"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-be2af266" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-da74aea0"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-3a6d0f87">Not all crystals like water, and will be damaged by water. This may result in small cracks, while others may dissolve completely. Keep the following away from water and they will last a lot longer in your care.<br></span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-qPjXN eYzxUD pf-77760e64 pf-r pf-r-eh" data-pf-type="Row" style="--pf-s-lg: 15px; --pf-s-md: 15px; --pf-s-sm: 15px; --pf-s-xs: 15px;"><div class="sc-pbYdQ jklmHY pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12"><div class="sc-pkUyL fTyjzF pf-2a417776" data-pf-type="Column"><p data-pf-type="Paragraph2" class="sc-pkvvt cbrLgP pf-02d22a41"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-ptSuy fnmilh pf-c71a02d2"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Kyanite /&nbsp;Angelite /&nbsp;Selenite /&nbsp;Desert Rose /&nbsp;Calcite /&nbsp;Cel